    <p style="chapterTitle">Estimating A Limit Numerically</p>

    <p style="title">INTRODUCTION</p>
    <p>
      When estimating a limit of a function as x approaches a constant, algebraic tools can usually be used to solve the limit. In this lesson, we will take a look at some examples of solving limits without graphs or tables.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!--Summary-->
  <sectionNoTitle>
    <stack>
      <style>
        <widthPercentage>0.93</widthPercentage>
        <horizontalAlignment>center</horizontalAlignment>
      </style>
      <style>
        <counter name="decBullet" format="decimal" />
      </style>

      <style name="numberedBullet">
        <increment counter="decBullet" />
        <numbering counter="decBullet" mode="flat" />
      </style>
      <p style="titleMargin">
        <b>Summary</b>
      </p>

      <p>If given a limit problem, we should use the following steps:</p>
      <p>
        <b>1: </b>Try solving the problem by inputting x into the problem.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>2: </b>If arrive at <image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/f663b41e66984624a0d14464e1328502.png" alt=" \frac{0}{0} " scale="0.0175" baseline="0.344841" inspect="false" />, try to use algebraic manipulation to solve for the limit as x approaches a constant.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>3: </b>If cannot use algebraic tools (factoring, conjugation, etc.) use a table or a graph to solve for the limit as x approaches a constant.
      </p>
      <p>However, first we should determine whether the problem can be solved without the need for a table.</p>
      <stack style="questionAnswer">

        <p style="title">Example</p>
        <p>solve: <image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/3072b98f67f34b4db4462cc103d09e0c.png" alt=" \lim_{x\rightarrow 2} (12x^2 - 3x + 8) " scale="0.0175" baseline="0.25" inspect="false" /></p>
        <p><image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/6b25b6e59ae943b8a679a155cd9c2903.png" alt=" (12(2)^2 - 3(2) + 8) = 50 " scale="0.0175" baseline="0" inspect="true" /></p>
      </stack>

      <p> Some limit questions can be tricky as they require more work.</p>
      <stack style="questionAnswer">
        <p style="title">Example</p>
        <p>solve: <image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/b4ccdcd1ab184e31b45c2accfa09ef27.png" alt=" \lim_{x\rightarrow -5} \frac{x^2 - 25}{x^2 + 2x - 15} " scale="0.0175" baseline="0.428175" inspect="false" /></p>
        <p>If we just plug-in -5, we will get 0/0, and thus will have to use the table method to solve this problem. However, if we look more closely, we can simplify the problem and then compute the limit again.</p>
        <p><image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/35dd721be8984c038b9c8443ec82f461.png" alt=" \lim_{x\rightarrow -5} \frac{x^2 - 25}{x^2 + 2x - 15} = \lim_{x\rightarrow -5} \frac{(x - 5)(x+5)}{(x - 3)(x + 5)} = \lim_{x\rightarrow -5} \frac{x-5}{x-3} " scale="0.0175" baseline="0" inspect="true" /></p>
        <p>We then plug-in -5 and arrive at <image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/8cb1200ace72450ba0f40a1608b469ae.png" alt=" \frac{-10}{-8} = \frac{5}{4} " scale="0.0175" baseline="0.428175" inspect="false" /></p>
      </stack>

      <!--Step by Step start-->
      <p style="titleMargin">
        <b>Step by Step</b>
      </p>
      <stack style="questionAnswer">
        <p style="title">Step by Step </p>
        <style name="ptag">
          <marginBottom>30</marginBottom>
          <marginTop>30</marginTop>
          <widthPercentage>0.80</widthPercentage>
          <horizontalAlignment>center</horizontalAlignment>
        </style>
        <table widths="10% 90%" grid="false">
          <row>
            <column>
              <image src="curriculumThemePack\question.png" inspect="false" />
            </column>
            <column>
              <p>Solve: <image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/719645eab1a9470f9639e4794ed3ba53.png" alt=" \lim_{x\rightarrow 4} \frac{3 - \sqrt{x+5}}{x-4} " scale="0.0175" baseline="0.428175" inspect="false" /></p>
            </column>
          </row>
        </table>
        <!--Wrap 1-->
        <stack style="collapsed" name="wrap1">
          <p style="ptag">
            Plug in x = 4 into the function.
          </p>

          <equation><image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/518b39e86abe4de58065eede04ea60b4.png" alt=" \lim_{x\rightarrow 4} \frac{3 - \sqrt{x+5}}{x-4} = \frac{0}{0} " scale="0.0175" baseline="0" inspect="true" /></equation>
          <p style="ptag">We have to simplify the equation using algebra. Eliminate the square root term by multiplying by the conjugate of the numerator over itself. </p>
        </stack>

        <!--Wrap 2-->
        <stack style="collapsed" name="wrap2">
          <p style="ptag">
            <b>  Then we get:  </b>
          </p>

          <equation><image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/19328ffaa45545eeaaf3257fb9392c39.png" alt=" = \lim_{x\rightarrow 4} \frac{3 - \sqrt{x+5}}{x-4}\times \frac{3 + \sqrt{x+5}}{3 + \sqrt{x+5}} " scale="0.0175" baseline="0" inspect="true" /></equation>
          <equation><image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/43e2f88c997a49b3b1fc5a647d42de04.png" alt=" = \lim_{x\rightarrow 4} \frac{9 - (x+5)}{(x-4)(3 + \sqrt{x+5})}" scale="0.0175" baseline="0" inspect="true" /> </equation>
          <equation><image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/bb37910a1d914984a6187990932a0ebe.png" alt=" = \lim_{x\rightarrow 4} \frac{4 - x}{(x-4)(3 + \sqrt{x+5})} " scale="0.0175" baseline="0" inspect="true" /></equation>
          <equation><image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/d7991169ab5e472fba2616dacc6d9467.png" alt=" = \lim_{x\rightarrow 4} \frac{-(x - 4)}{(x-4)(3 + \sqrt{x+5})} " scale="0.0175" baseline="0" inspect="true" /></equation>

          <p style="ptag">Divide out the factors (x-4), which cause the indeterminate form <image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/7c90d6310ad74b68b03645f181065323.png" alt=" \frac{0}{0}. " scale="0.0175" baseline="0.344841" inspect="false" /></p>

          <equation><image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/9a0fdc17bb7d4419b0573d6032afa4a1.png" alt=" = \lim_{x\rightarrow 4} \frac{-1}{(3 + \sqrt{x+5})} " scale="0.0175" baseline="0" inspect="true" /></equation>
        </stack>

        <!--Wrap 3-->
        <stack style="collapsed" name="wrap3">
          <p style="ptag">
            <b>Now the limit can be computed!</b>
          </p>

          <equation><image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/9a0fdc17bb7d4419b0573d6032afa4a1.png" alt=" = \lim_{x\rightarrow 4} \frac{-1}{(3 + \sqrt{x+5})} " scale="0.0175" baseline="0" inspect="true" /></equation>
          <equation><image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/ff1dd3761af04b09b10c46951e517013.png" alt=" = \frac{-1}{(3 + \sqrt{4+5})} " scale="0.0175" baseline="0" inspect="true" /></equation>
          <equation><image xmlns="http://resources.qdexapps.com/schema/v1/QDocument.xsd" src="Equations/85dd91d5bbea44bd8fd890346bdfa0d5.png" alt=" = -\frac{1}{6} " scale="0.0175" baseline="0" inspect="true" /></equation>
        </stack>
        <script>
          local x = 0;

        </script>

        <button style="large" name="button1" content="Step 1">
          <style>
            <widthPercentage>0.6</widthPercentage>
            <marginTop>30</marginTop>
          </style>
          <onClick>
            if x == 0 then
            wrap1.Style.Visibility = "visible";
            button1.Text = "Step 2"
            x = x+1
            return x;
            end

            if x == 1 then
            wrap2.Style.Visibility = "visible";
            button1.Text = "Final Step"
            x = x+1
            return x;
            end


            if x == 2 then
            wrap3.Style.Visibility = "visible";
            button1.Text = "Hide Answer"
            x = x+1
            return x;
            end

            if x == 3 then
            wrap1.Style.Visibility = "collapsed";
            wrap2.Style.Visibility = "collapsed";
            wrap3.Style.Visibility = "collapsed";
            button1.Text = "Step 1"
            x = 0
            return x;
            end


          </onClick>
        </button>
      </stack>
    </stack>

